column_description: The Policy Identifier that Customer receives
Policy Period ID
The Quote Identifier that Customer receives
The name of a policy transaction (i.e policy job), e.g. Cancellation / Policy Change / Reinstatement / Submission / Renewal
A business identifier of a job, if the job is submission, then job number will be the same as quote number.

The status of a job. For Cancellation / Reinstatement / Policy Change, the policy Status will always be Bound. For Submission, status could be quoted or bound (or any other final status e.g. Decline, Withdrawn, Not Taken). For Renewal, status could be Renewing or Bound (or any other final status e.g. Not-Taken, Not Renewed, Withdrawn)
Always going to be {partner}
The name of the product, it could be Home / Car / Landlord.
The producer of the policy, it follows the pattern of {partner}_PARTNER_{Product}
The term number of a policy. For policy migrated from QBE to IAG, the term number of migration renewal term will start from 1.
Indicate if it is a New Business or Renewal. For Policy migrated from QBE to IAG, the term type would be "Renewal".
The start date of the policy term
The end date of the policy term.
The date this period was created. For Reinstatement, it will be the create date the policy period that reinstatement job trying to reinstated.
The effective date a policy transaction / job is taking effective. It could be either future dated or back dated.

The finalization date of a policy transaction. It will ONLY be populated when a policy transaction achieves a final status (e.g. Bound, Not Taken, Decline). However, {partner} have requested IF this is NULL, then populate the Written_date's value into this field so to help design CDC
The State the Policy Period is based in.
Always going to be Partner for {partner}.

The channel an {partner} sales (i.e. a submission transaction) starts, it could be either Online or Contact Centre. Online may refer to sales started from Partner Branch or Web. Contact Centre refers to IAG Contact Centre. For Migration Renewal from QBE to {partner}, the channel will be  populated as 'Contact Centre'.
The channel an {partner} sales finalised. It will be populated with a value if the sales finalised in a different channel to the sales starts, otherwise it will be NULL.

The Derived originating channel as per {partner} required - If originating channel = Contact center then IAG Contact Centre If originating channel = Online (i.e. Partner's Web / branch / contact center) - then  Digital - when originating branch code is null Partner Contact Centre - When originating branch code is in {partner}'s 'Contact Centre'  hierachy Partner Branch - When originating branch code is in {partner}'s Australian Branch Network Otherwise 'Unknown'
Refer above originating channel name update

The branch / contact centre Identifier passed on from {partner} which can help identifier an {partner} branch or an {partner} contact center. The code will populate the information that a customer starts its submission.

Same concept as originating_branch_code, however it will be the identifier when {partner} sales is being finalised. Comparison between Originating and Completing branch code / channel name could identifier if there is any shift of sales channel and/or sales branch.
The channel a Policy Transaction will be initiated.
The channel a Policy Transaction will be finalised.
A Y/N indicate to indicate the policy has been migrated from an external source to IAG's PolicyCenter.
The Heritage System's Policy identifier. For QBE's migrated policy, this will be the policy_number field from QBE's policy common file.

The start date of a Policy's lifecycle, for QBE's migrated policy, it will be QBE's original_start_date from QBE's policy common file. For non QBE's migrated policy, it will be the policy start date with IAG.
A Y/N to indicate of Customer choose the Pay later option
A Y/N to indicate if a customer has made the payment for a policy term. IF a policy is via instalments, it indicate whether IAG receives the first instatement amount from a customer.
The date IAG receives the customer's payment. For an instalments policy, it indicates the date IAG receives the customer's first instatement amount.

The type of a cancellation, could be either "Flat" (cancellation date is the same as policy's term start date) OR "Mid Term" (cancellation date greater than the policy term start date). This field will only be populated for a cancellation job.
The date the cancellation is taking effective.
The sub category of a cancellation type. It provides reason for a cancellation.
The reason customer provided if a Renewal is in non renewal / withdrawn status.
The reason customer provided if a Renewal Offer has been declined by a customer
Whether it is an annual policy OR non annual (mostly applicable to Travel product).
The number of months for a policy.
The primary insured name on the policy.

The Identifier of the person created the policy transaction. sXXXX refers the transaction is created by an IAG person, pbXXX refers to the transaction created by a Partner staff, pu/bu/su refer to a transaction created by system.
The employee number of a partner staff. The number should be passed from Partner {partner}

The Identifier of the person updated the policy transaction. sXXXX refers the transaction is created by an IAG person, pbXXX refers to the transaction created by a Partner staff, pu/bu/su refer to a transaction created by system.
The employee number of a partner staff. The number should be passed from Partner {partner}
The frequency of billing / instalments frequency.
The method of a billing.
The Transaction premium for the policy transaction, inclusive of partner commission amount.
Tax and Charges amount for a policy transaction.
Tax and Charges amount for a policy transaction.
Tax and Charges amount for a policy transaction.

The prior term's annualised premium. This field will NOT populate the QBE's prior term price for the migration renewal term... it will only populate the Prior term's value for IAG's Native Renewal. {partner} agree to stitch in {partner}'s own warehouse to obtain the QBE's prior term renewal price.
Tax and Charges amount for prior term.
Tax and Charges amount for prior term.
Tax and Charges amount for prior term.
The correspondence address a customer prefers for a Policy
The correspondence address a customer prefers for a Policy

The email address of Customer's correspondence email, at quoted status, it could populate the Customer's quote follow up email address (if Customer did not provide quote follow up email address, then it would be default to Customer's correspondence email).
Email Document Consent
The Instalment amount for the Policy Term, will only show if Policy is NOT an annual pay policy, amount including Tax and Charges as requested by {partner} team
The dollar amount for an adjustments / discretionary amount

Column to reflect Discount information. If $0 THEN Policy had staff benefit applied (applicable to Renewing / Quoted / Bound status), if <> $0 THEN sum of the applicable discount (online and/or offer), else null. As of Sept. 2023, the exact discount (apart from staff benefit)/ campaign is remaining as a future proofing concept, hence this field requires review and future uplift when {partner} / CGU enables discount and campaign. {partner} agree to use the Staff benefit applied component in this attribute as a REFERENCE ONLY, given Staff benefit is applied through 0% commission, {partner} has agreed to reference the staff benefit applied component in this attribute as a 'REFERENCE ONLY' concept, i.e. at any point in time or occasion, the source of commission amount would be from Commission Statement and Flatfile, IF there is an internal / external audit, {partner} would seek with CGU for information to support rather than solely relying on this column.
